lead_paragraph: Kyle Lowry scored 26 points, including five 3-pointers, DeMar DeRozan added 22 points and the Toronto Raptors held off Phoenix 104-97 Tuesday night, spoiling the debut of Suns interim coach Earl Watson.

headline.print_headline: Lowry, Raptors Hold Off Suns, Spoil Watson's Coaching Debut
